Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the @water{200%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#pot lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{100%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still
covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #large bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Breadcrumbs{10%g}, @Salt for the
Meatballs{1/4%tsp} and @Water for the Breadcrumbs{2%tbsp}, then add the
@British Pork Mince{240%g}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized
balls, 5 per person, then pop onto a #large baking tray{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your
hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and
cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no
longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @Courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into
1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the
courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn only every couple
of mins.

Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer the courgette to a
bowl and cover to keep warm.

Pop the (now empty) #pan{} back on medium heat with another drizzle of oil. Add
the @Tomato Puree{30%g}, @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet} and
@Korma Curry Paste{50%g}, then fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Water for the Sauce{200%ml} and a
pinch of @sugar{pinch} (if you have any). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat
and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful
at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

When the meatballs are ready, gently stir them into the curry sauce along with
the charred courgette. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{} and spoon over the curry to
finish. Enjoy!